headlines.description: — Trae Young made all of his 21 free throws and scored 35 points to lead the Atlanta Hawks to their fourth straight victory, 123-110 over the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young makes all 21 free throws and scores 35 points in Hawks' 123-110 win over Hornets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 34 and Chet Holmgren had 23 points and 15 rebounds to help the Oklahoma City Thunder clinch a playoff berth by beating the Boston Celtics 118-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: West-best Thunder come to home of NBA champs and beat Celtics to clinch playoff berth

headlines.description: — AJ Lawson scored 28 points, Jared Rhoden set career highs with 25 points and 12 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat the Philadelphia 76ers 118-105 on Wednesday night in a matchup of short-handed teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lawson, Rhoden and Robinson help Raptors beat 76ers 118-105 for 5th win in 6 games

headlines.description: — Bogdan Bogdanovic scored a season-high 30 points and Ivica Zubac added 26 points and 14 rebounds, helping the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Miami Heat 119-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic scores 30, Zubac adds 26 and Clippers roll past Heat 119-104

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 29 points to lead the Houston Rockets to a 111-104 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Wednesday night in a game where Houston’s Steven Adams and Phoenix’s Mason Plumlee were ejected for fighting.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green leads Rockets past Suns in game marred by fight between Adams, Plumlee

headlines.description: — Luke Kennard scored 30 points and Ja Morant had 28, helping the Memphis Grizzlies top the Utah Jazz 122-115 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kennard and Morant convert late 3-pointers to lead Grizzlies past Jazz 122-115

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox had 32 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds and the San Antonio Spurs snapped a three-game skid, beating the injury-depleted Dallas Mavericks 126-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox has 32 points, 11 assists, 9 rebounds in Spurs' win over injury-depleted Mavs

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 29 points, Julius Randle added 25 and the Minnesota Timberwolves extended their winning streak to six games by routing the Denver Nuggets 115-95 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 29 points and Julius Randle adds 25 as Timberwolves rout Nuggets 115-95

events.name: New York Knicks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges hit a 25-foot 3-pointer at the buzzer to give the New York Knicks a 114-113 overtime win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges nails 3-pointer at buzzer to give Knicks a 114-113 OT win over the Trail Blazers
